  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Performing a reference architecture fit-gap analysis can take between 1 day and 2 weeks.&amp;nbsp; Factors that influence&#xD;
    the effort required include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Whether the reference architecture is selected from a single architectural asset base or involves searching&#xD;
        multiple locations.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How well documented the reference architecture is and, if two or more are being compared, how consistently they are&#xD;
        documented.&amp;nbsp; In particular how easy is it to identify subject areas covered by the reference architecture?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The quality and completeness of the system requirements.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The extent to which the statement-of-fit must include the specification of deltas from the asset.&amp;nbsp; (Typically,&#xD;
        requirements for deltas are identified at this point, but not specified in detail until later.)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If the architectural asset being considered is not a reference architecture but is the actual architecture of another&#xD;
    similar project, this is likely to increase the effort as it will not be documented for&#xD;
    reuse.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
